Package com.esplibrary.utilities

Class ByteList

java.lang.Object
com.esplibrary.utilities.ByteList
public class ByteList extends Object
A custom primitive byte collection class that does not cause auto-boxing when storing and retrieving elements.

    • clear

      public boolean clear()
      Resets the list count back to zero. This will not actually clear the internal data set. Since this list wraps around primitive array, we do not need to loop through the data set and manually set the indexes to null. We can cheat and get a performance boost at the expense of having a couple dozen bytes remaining in heap.
      Returns:
      Always returns true.

    • clear

      public boolean clear(boolean resize)
      Resets the internal data set and the list count back to zero. Be wary, this slightly less performant than @see ByteList#clear(). This has further peformance implications when calling andy of the @see ByteList#add()* methods because it will require the array to grown to an acommadating size.
      Parameters:
      resize - Indicates if you'd like this array to be resized to its initial size of zero.
